🧾 Features:
Feature	Description
Show_id	Unique ID
Type	Movie / TV Show
Title	Name of content
Director	Director name
Cast	Actors
Country	Production country
Date_added	Added on Netflix
Release_year	Year of release
Rating	Content rating
Duration	Time / Seasons
Listed_in	Genre
Description	Summary
📊 Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
🔍 Key Insights:
🎯 TV-MA is the most common rating (~2861 titles)
🎬 Movies dominate Netflix content:
Movies: 69.14%
TV Shows: 30.86%
🎥 Top Directors:
Raúl Campos
Jan Suter
🌍 USA produces most content
🇮🇳 India produces more movies than TV shows
📅 Content production increased rapidly after 2000
<p align="center"> <img src="https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/67974590/217807093-0b14b879-bcb7-414f-a6fe-f36596256030.png"> </p>
🤖 Machine Learning Models
1️⃣ K-Means Clustering
Partitions data into K clusters
Each point belongs to nearest centroid
Iteratively updates cluster centers
<p align="center"> <img src="https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/67974590/217806001-38711a86-0648-4683-9d88-d4994c0888fb.jpg" width="70%"> </p>
2️⃣ Agglomerative Hierarchical Clustering
Bottom-up approach
Each point starts as its own cluster
Merges closest clusters step-by-step
Visualized using Dendrogram
<p align="center"> <img src="https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/67974590/217806548-2e8af3bf-a994-4f70-82c8-2f1294afd652.png"> </p>
